column3: Just because it's not used doesn't mean it should be void'd...\n

I don't really have an opinion on this. On one hand it indeed makes no sense to return something that isn't used, on the other hand it's not like this allows removing a significant amount of dead code, and it may come in useful later.\n

utACK - I added the return value because it was cheap and sounded potentially useful, but I doubt it will be used.

Please squash the commits though.
